Hi Haddad,
Unit testing threads can be difficult.  Hopefully, one of the forthcoming
books will focus on testing patterns.  While you wait, you can check out the
information on http://c2.com/cgi/wiki?ExtremeProgrammingChallengeFourteen -
concurrency.  Most things can be tested if you&#39;re determined enough.

When you write a test, it is always useful to consider &quot;what does my code
need to guarrantee here&quot;.  It seems to me like you could verify that the
&quot;Machinelistener&quot; was among the active threads in the VM between the
constructor and the call to switch-off.  I can&#39;t really say, though, it&#39;s
your code.


Sincerely,
Johannes Brodwall
